  "conclusion": "H010 closes descriptor geometry. H012 closes DMAC bit 0x200 as a mainline-only clue. H013 clears the prior lab PIO rail's ACCESS_BY_AHB contamination and proves clean DMA access mode alone is insufficient. H014 identifies the remaining vendor-visible GCTRL bit 0x00000800 as SDXC_DTIME_UNIT, a v5p3x read-data-timeout scaling bit that pairs with TMOUT=0x01312dff during vendor reads and recovers to TMOUT=0xffffffff. Visible descriptor geometry, DMAC, and GCTRL bits are now exhausted for this blocker; next work moves to hidden wrapper, DMA coherency, or storage-fabric evidence."
